**Git Advanced Commands Notes**

1. Push Changes to GitHub
Upload local commits to GitHub

Command:
git push origin main


2. Fetch and Merge Changes from Remote
Download latest changes and merge automatically

Command:
git pull origin main


3. Create a Pull Request (PR)
Request to merge your branch into main branch

Process:
- Push branch to GitHub
- Open GitHub
- Click "Compare & Pull Request"
- Create Pull Request


4. Create a New Branch
Create separate workspace

Command:
git checkout -b feature-name


5. Delete Remote Branch
Remove branch from GitHub

Command:
git push origin --delete branch-name


6. PR (Pull Request)
Used for:
- Code review
- Team collaboration
- Safe merging
- Production workflow


7. Fetch Changes Without Merging
Download updates only

Command:
git fetch

Difference:
fetch = See changes only
pull = download + merge


8. Clone with the Latest Commits Only
Download lightweight repository

Command:
git clone --depth 1 repository-link


9. View File Modification History
See commit history of specific file

Command:
git log filename

Example:
git log index.html
or
git log --online


10. Resolve Merge Conflicts
When two branches modify same code

Steps:
- Edit conflicted code manually
- Save file
- Stage changes

Commands:
git add .
git commit -m "Resolved merge conflict"
